ackup-photos-using-a-wireless-card-reader\">Backup photos using a wireless Card Reader<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A wireless card reader is very useful if you are not taking a laptop. If you pick a good card reader like a <a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/1ZYQ6vY\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Kingston Wireless<\/a>, you can plug in your memory card at one side and a portable hard drive on the other. You can transfer photos to your portable hard drive by using a phone or tablet <a href=\"https:\/\/itunes.apple.com\/us\/app\/kingston-mobilelite\/id628221903?mt=8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">MobileLite<\/a> app to connect to your card reader using WiFi. This is offline WiFi, which is just a signal between the devices like Bluetooth. See our photo below or <a href=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=4CvzFJbuFuw\">this<\/a> demo.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/backup-photos-while-traveling-kingston-wireless-salt-in-our-hair.jpg\" alt=\"Backup photos while traveling ipad\"><\/noscript><img width=\"450\" height=\"338\" alt=\"Backup photos while traveling ipad\" class=\"wp-image-860 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/23165507\/backup-photos-while-traveling-kingston-wireless-salt-in-our-hair.jpg 1080w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/23165507\/backup-photos-while-traveling-kingston-wireless-salt-in-our-hair-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/23165507\/backup-photos-while-traveling-kingston-wireless-salt-in-our-hair-600x450.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/23165507\/backup-photos-while-traveling-kingston-wireless-salt-in-our-hair-450x338.jpg 450w, https:\/\/static.sa